# Page Context Feature Parity

## Background

The `pageContext` feature exists in two places in platform override files:

1. **Standalone `pageContext` feature** (top-level in `features`) — consumed by content-scope-scripts (C-S-S) for page content extraction
2. **`aiChat.features.pageContext` sub-feature** — consumed by native apps to enable/disable page context integration in AI Chat

Both must be kept in sync. If the native app enables `aiChat.features.pageContext` but the standalone C-S-S `pageContext` feature is disabled (or vice versa), page context silently fails at runtime.

## Rules

### 1. State parity between C-S-S and native

When enabling or disabling `pageContext` on any platform, **both** entries must be updated:

- `features.pageContext.state` (C-S-S)
- `features.aiChat.features.pageContext.state` (native)

If one is `"enabled"`, the other must also be `"enabled"` (or at minimum `"preview"` / `"internal"` at the same level).

### 2. Required C-S-S settings

The standalone `pageContext` feature **must** include these settings on all platforms where it is enabled:

| Setting | Required | Notes |
|---------|----------|-------|
| `maxContentLength` | Yes | Typically `9500` |
| `mainContentSelector` | Yes | Use `"main, article, .content, .main, #content, #main"` |
| `excludeSelectors` | Yes | Standard set: `.ad`, `.sidebar`, `.footer`, `.nav`, `.header`, `.banner`, `.popup` |

### 3. Cross-platform conditional changes

Domain-specific conditional changes should be consistent across platforms. If a domain override is added to one platform (e.g., `nba.com`, `reddit.com`), check whether it should also apply to other platforms.

Current shared conditional changes:

| Domain | Patch | Platforms |
|--------|-------|-----------|
| `nba.com` | `mainContentSelector` → `"main"` | macOS, iOS, Android, Windows |
| `reddit.com` | Add `shreddit-comments-page-ad` to `excludeSelectors` | macOS, Windows |

### 4. Checklist for pageContext changes

Before committing changes to any `pageContext` configuration:

- [ ] Standalone `pageContext` state matches `aiChat.features.pageContext` state
- [ ] `mainContentSelector` is present in C-S-S settings
- [ ] Domain conditional changes are consistent across platforms
- [ ] Build succeeds (`node index.js`)
- [ ] Tests pass (`npm test`)

## Files

- **Base feature**: `features/page-context.json`
- **Platform overrides**: `overrides/{windows,macos,ios,android}-override.json`
- **C-S-S implementation**: [`content-scope-scripts/injected/src/features/page-context.js`](https://github.com/duckduckgo/content-scope-scripts/blob/main/injected/src/features/page-context.js)
- **C-S-S platform support**: [`content-scope-scripts/injected/src/features.js`](https://github.com/duckduckgo/content-scope-scripts/blob/main/injected/src/features.js) — `platformSupport`
